      <h2>Marketing priorities for pet product stores</h2>
      <p>Pet product stores break when email treats every subscriber the same. The pressure point is pet lifecycle, reorder timing, and product education. A disciplined email marketing program must coordinate consent, lifecycle timing, product context, and margin-aware measurement — not blast more coupons.</p>
      <p>Priority plays: Pet life-stage segmentation; Reorder by consumption math; Breed/size-specific recommendations; New pet onboarding series. Document suppressions for recent purchasers, wholesale accounts, and active support cases before scaling sends.</p>
      <p>Sequenzy ranks first for pet product stores because lifecycle editorial beats newsletter volume: welcome by signup source, replenishment matched to consumption, winback with VIP exclusions.</p>
      <p>Klaviyo remains the benchmark when pet product stores need predictive segmentation and native Shopify event depth at scale. Omnisend wins when email + SMS must go live before month end.</p>
